HEADWORD: Insperse
<hw>In*sperse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inspersus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>inspergere</ets> to sprinkle upon;
pref. <ets>in-</ets> in, on + <ets>spargere</ets> to sprinkle.]</ety>
<def>To sprinkle; to scatter.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inspersion</ent>⟦br⟧
